{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccs3QTdfKBnhZPaHbUY7u","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `TCP 200` log entry confirms the SQL passthrough on port 26257 successfully proxied the connection from the curl-test pod (10.244.0.198) to CockroachDB. Everything is verified working:\n\n**Summary:**\n1. **DB Console (HTTPS)**: Created `Ingress` `crdb-ui` in the `cockroachdb` namespace (`ingressClassName: nginx`) routing `crdb-ui.example.com` → `crdb-cluster-public:8080`, with TLS via the `crdb-ui-tls` secret. That secret originally held placeholder (`dummy-crt`/`dummy-key`) non-PEM data, so I regenerated it with a real self-signed cert for `CN=crdb-ui.example.com`. Verified: `curl -k --resolve` returns `HTTP_STATUS:200`.\n2. **SQL (TCP passthrough)**: Created a `tcp-services` ConfigMap in `ingress-nginx` mapping port `26257` → `cockroachdb/crdb-cluster-public:26257`, wired it into the controller via `--tcp-services-configmap` arg, added `containerPort 26257` to the controller pod, and exposed port `26257` on the `ingress-nginx-controller` Service (NodePort `30469`). Verified: TCP connection to the ingress service on 26257 was accepted and proxied to CockroachDB (controller log shows `TCP 200` access entry)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":500,"cache_read_input_tokens":47630,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":500},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"487a554b-1a0e-474a-92e7-52f0b6a7437f","uuid":"9568a42c-c21f-486a-9d6c-904950987dc2","request_id":"req_011Ccs3QSKHWoiiJaJN3zxao"}
